00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:06.480
Fans go crazy for a good superhero movie.

00:00:06.480 --> 00:00:10.240
For years, characters and stories from the
pages of Marvel, DC, Dark Horse, Image and

00:00:10.240 --> 00:00:13.510
many more comic book companies have been gracing
the big screen.The genre is so unique and

00:00:13.510 --> 00:00:14.510
varied that it can include moments of amazing
action, side-splitting hilarity, raw sexiness,

00:00:14.510 --> 00:00:15.510
endless references to other superheroes and
much, much more - and that results in viewers

00:00:15.510 --> 00:00:19.310
keeping a very close eye on the movies within
it.In turn, that can result in a lot of pausing.

00:00:19.310 --> 00:00:23.480
Whether it's to marvel at something spectacular,
bask in the beauty of a particular character,

00:00:23.480 --> 00:00:27.850
or spot a fun Easter egg, fans are constantly
revelling in certain moments in superhero

00:00:27.850 --> 00:00:30.260
movies - and that's what this video is all
about.

00:00:30.260 --> 00:00:38.850
Here are the ten most paused scenes in popular
superhero movies.

00:00:38.850 --> 00:00:42.940
The Train Scene in Spider-Man 2
We begin our list with a funny entry.

00:00:42.940 --> 00:00:47.469
2004's Spider-Man 2 remains one of the most
faithful and outright best comic book movies

00:00:47.469 --> 00:00:48.469
to date.

00:00:48.469 --> 00:00:52.440
Tobey Maguire shone in his best performance
as the titular hero, while Alfred Molina gave

00:00:52.440 --> 00:00:56.149
one of the best villain performances of all
time in a superhero movie - and it's a scene

00:00:56.149 --> 00:00:59.860
involving them both that we're referring to
here.Molina's Doctor Octopus had sabotaged

00:00:59.860 --> 00:01:03.949
the controls of a train, leaving it unable
to break and Spider-Man to save the passengers.

00:01:03.949 --> 00:01:07.890
Using his webbing and all of his strength,
Spidey saved the day - but the strained faces

00:01:07.890 --> 00:01:12.610
Tobey Maguire was making were hilarious and
people loved pausing on them to have a good

00:01:12.610 --> 00:01:16.000
laugh.

00:01:16.000 --> 00:01:20.040
Naked Mystique in X-Men: The Last Stand
Prior to Jennifer Lawrence taking over the

00:01:20.040 --> 00:01:24.400
role in the new X-Men movie timeline, the
equally sexy Rebecca Romijn played Mystique

00:01:24.400 --> 00:01:25.400
in the franchise.

00:01:25.400 --> 00:01:28.920
She looked incredible in the the blue make-up
that created the character's look - but it's

00:01:28.920 --> 00:01:33.150
a scene without said make-up that is one of
the most paused in superhero movie history.In

00:01:33.150 --> 00:01:38.549
2006's X-Men: The Last Stand, Romijn's Mystique
is injected with the mutant "cure", resulting

00:01:38.549 --> 00:01:40.200
in her blue skin disappearing.

00:01:40.200 --> 00:01:44.119
This left the character looking completely
human - and completely naked.

00:01:44.119 --> 00:01:48.170
Viewers around the world looked on in awe
as Romijn laid on the ground in her birthday

00:01:48.170 --> 00:01:55.110
suit - and they paused en masse to get a better
look.

00:01:55.110 --> 00:01:58.791
Captain America's Shield in Iron Man
These days, seeing Captain America's shield

00:01:58.791 --> 00:02:02.360
in the Marvel Cinematic Universe is no big
deal - Captain America had his first solo

00:02:02.360 --> 00:02:06.360
movie five years ago and Chris Evans has become
a prominent part of the franchise as the super

00:02:06.360 --> 00:02:11.060
soldier since then - but back in 2008 he hadn't
even been mentioned.That changed in Iron Man,

00:02:11.060 --> 00:02:14.840
when a partially completed replica of the
shield was seen in Tony Stark's laboratory,

00:02:14.840 --> 00:02:17.310
resulting in lots of pausing on the part of
the viewer.

00:02:17.310 --> 00:02:21.310
It should also be noted that Captain America
could be seen under the ice in a deleted scene

00:02:21.310 --> 00:02:25.470
in The Incredible Hulk later that year - something
a lot of people have pressed pause on since

00:02:25.470 --> 00:02:28.959
it was made public.

00:02:28.959 --> 00:02:33.650
"Thor" in The Incredible Hulk
Prior to Captain America's first appearance

00:02:33.650 --> 00:02:37.510
in the Marvel Cinematic Universe, the next
Avenger to follow Iron Man and the Hulk into

00:02:37.510 --> 00:02:40.730
the franchise was Thor in his 2011 solo movie.

00:02:40.730 --> 00:02:45.280
This resulting in some retrospective pausing
of a scene in 2008's The Incredible Hulk,

00:02:45.280 --> 00:02:48.880
when viewers thought they saw Thor making
a brief cameo.It came in the scene when the

00:02:48.880 --> 00:02:52.250
Hulk and Betty Ross are in a cave and there's
a thunderstorm going on.

00:02:52.250 --> 00:02:56.170
Viewers thought the storm was caused by the
God of Thunder's arrival on Earth and swore

00:02:56.170 --> 00:02:59.010
blind that they saw him fall to the ground
in the background.

00:02:59.010 --> 00:03:03.310
Of course, they turned out to be wrong, but
a lot of pausing went on when people believed

00:03:03.310 --> 00:03:08.069
they had seen him.

00:03:08.069 --> 00:03:12.330
Nite Owl and Silk Spectre in Watchmen
As with the audiences of any movie genre,

00:03:12.330 --> 00:03:15.510
comic book movie viewers love a good sex scene
- and they were treated to one of the more

00:03:15.510 --> 00:03:18.250
revealing examples in comic book movie history
in 2009's Watchmen.

00:03:18.250 --> 00:03:19.250
The scene in question was a sex scene between
Patrick Wilson's Daniel Dreiberg AKA Nite

00:03:19.250 --> 00:03:20.680
Owl II and Malin Åkerman's Laurie Juspeczyk
AKA Silk Spectre II.It happens on board Dreiberg's

00:03:20.680 --> 00:03:24.239
Owlship and Åkerman's breasts were completely
