00:03:27.270 --> 00:03:33.159
world, as viewers honed in for a better look.

00:03:33.159 --> 00:03:36.910
Scarlett Johansson's Face in The Avengers
It's always comforting to find out that even

00:03:36.910 --> 00:03:40.330
the most beautiful people can be caught off
guard looking less than attractive, so when

00:03:40.330 --> 00:03:44.340
that happened to the gorgeous Scarlett Johansson
in 2012's The Avengers, a lot of people were

00:03:44.340 --> 00:03:47.799
eager to see - especially her fellow females!Johansson's
Black Widow was caught looking a lot... well...

00:03:47.799 --> 00:03:51.830
uglier than usual in the scene in which she
commandeered a Chitauri aircraft.

00:03:51.830 --> 00:03:55.270
As she went to cut a cord holding a Chitauri
henchman in place, she made a face that only

00:03:55.270 --> 00:03:56.409
her mother could love!

00:03:56.409 --> 00:03:59.879
It's a scene that has been paused many times
- and been used in countless memes - ever

00:03:59.879 --> 00:04:03.000
since it was first seen.

00:04:03.000 --> 00:04:07.159
The Collector's Collection in Guardians of
the Galaxy

00:04:07.159 --> 00:04:12.120
Superhero movie fans love a good Easter egg
and, these days, spend just as much time looking

00:04:12.120 --> 00:04:15.689
for them as they do enjoying the plot of the
movie - and the most Easter egg-rich scene

00:04:15.689 --> 00:04:19.900
in comic book movie history came in 2014's
Guardians of the Galaxy.The scene we're referring

00:04:19.900 --> 00:04:22.830
to is, of course, the one in The Collector's
museum on Knowhere.

00:04:22.830 --> 00:04:26.910
Benicio del Toro's character owned a lot of
interesting species and items - and eagle-eyed

00:04:26.910 --> 00:04:30.090
viewers loved spotting them, which resulted
in a lot of pausing.

00:04:30.090 --> 00:04:34.500
The likes of Howard the Duck, Adam Warlock's
cocoon, a Dark Elf and the slug creatures

00:04:34.500 --> 00:04:40.970
from Slither are just some of the things that
could be seen in there.

00:04:40.970 --> 00:04:43.910
The Avengers Jump Into Action in Avengers:
Age of Ultron

00:04:43.910 --> 00:04:48.780
At the start of 2015's Avengers: Age of Ultron,
there was an epic scene in which the six original

00:04:48.780 --> 00:04:53.100
members of the titular team storm Baron Strucker's
HYDRA base to retrieve the scepter that was

00:04:53.100 --> 00:04:57.400
previously wielded by Loki in the first Avengers
movie.As the team cut through Strucker's forces

00:04:57.400 --> 00:05:01.840
like a hot knife through butter, there's one
epic moment in which they all jump into shot

00:05:01.840 --> 00:05:05.750
together - and it's a shot that prompted the
use of millions of pause buttons around the

00:05:05.750 --> 00:05:06.750
world.

00:05:06.750 --> 00:05:11.240
Iron Man is flying, Captain America is on
a motorcyle and Thor, Hawkeye, Black Widow

00:05:11.240 --> 00:05:15.690
and Hulk are all leaping - it looks awesome.

00:05:15.690 --> 00:05:23.520
"The Wasp" in Ant-Man
In 2015's Ant-Man, viewers learned that Janet

00:05:23.520 --> 00:05:28.210
van Dyne - the original Wasp - disappeared
into the subatomic quantum realm while disabling

00:05:28.210 --> 00:05:32.199
a Soviet nuclear missile many years before
the events of the movie.At the end of the

00:05:32.199 --> 00:05:36.770
movie, Paul Rudd's Scott Lang also had to
go subatomic to defeat Corey Stoll's Yellowjacket

00:05:36.770 --> 00:05:40.630
- and viewers noticed something very interesting
while he was in the quantum realm.

00:05:40.630 --> 00:05:44.580
It was an outline that looked very much like
the original Wasp - prompting lots of viewers

00:05:44.580 --> 00:05:52.830
to hit pause to make their own assumptions
about whether or not it was really her.

00:05:52.830 --> 00:05:57.780
Harley Quinn Getting Dressed in Suicide Squad
2016's Suicide Squad received very mixed reviews

00:05:57.780 --> 00:06:01.400
from critics and fans alike - but one thing
everyone can agree on is that Margot Robbie

00:06:01.400 --> 00:06:03.090
looked absolutely incredible.

00:06:03.090 --> 00:06:06.520
With that in mind, this particular entry in
our most-paused moments list should come as

00:06:06.520 --> 00:06:10.220
no surprise.It's the scene in which Harley
gets changed into her costume and a large

00:06:10.220 --> 00:06:12.060
group of men watch on in awe.

00:06:12.060 --> 00:06:15.940
The camera pans all the way up her body and
just about catches a glimpse of her bra as

00:06:15.940 --> 00:06:18.180
she pulls her top down over her torso.

00:06:18.180 --> 00:06:22.750
Men around the world - and indeed some women
- paused that scene over and over and over

00:06:22.750 --> 00:06:25.970
and over again.

